# ============================================================
# PolyJarvis LAMMPS Engine - NEMD Müller-Plathe with Supercell Template
# ============================================================
# Method: RNEMD Müller-Plathe on a replicated supercell
#   Ref:  Müller-Plathe, J. Chem. Phys. 106, 6082 (1997)
#         Zhang et al., J. Phys. Chem. B 109, 15060 (2005)
#
# Purpose:
#   Polymer simulation boxes are often nearly cubic. For NEMD, the box
#   must be long along the heat flux axis (>= 40 Ang). This template
#   handles systems that need replication along NEMD_AXIS before running
#   (e.g., replicate 3x along z while keeping x,y at 1x).
#
#   IMPORTANT: Replication must be done OUTSIDE LAMMPS via RadonPy's
#   poly.super_cell() BEFORE generating this script. The data file passed
#   in should already be the replicated cell. This template documents
#   that expectation and uses geometry that matches the replicated box.
#
# When to use vs. nemd_thermal:
#   - nemd_thermal: Box is already long enough (>= 40 Ang) along NEMD_AXIS
#   - nemd_supercell: Equilibrated box is too short; needs replication first
#
# Physics identical to nemd_thermal (Müller-Plathe RNEMD):
#   - SHAKE must be OFF
#   - Timestep 0.2 fs
#   - NVE + fix thermal/conductivity
#   - Same unit conversion and kappa formula
#
# Additional placeholders vs. nemd_thermal:
#   {SUPERCELL_NOTE}   - informational comment about replication factor used
#   {NEMD_REP}         - replication factor along NEMD_AXIS (for documentation)
#   {NEMD_REP_OTHER}   - replication factor along other axes (for documentation)
#
# All other placeholders same as nemd_thermal.
# ============================================================

log {LOG_FILE} {LOG_APPEND}
units real
atom_style full
boundary p p p

# --- Supercell note ---
# {SUPERCELL_NOTE}
# Box replicated {NEMD_REP}x along {NEMD_AXIS}, {NEMD_REP_OTHER}x along other axes
# Replication performed by RadonPy poly.super_cell() before this script

# --- Force Field ---
{PAIR_STYLE_BLOCK}
dielectric 1.0
bond_style {BOND_STYLE}
angle_style {ANGLE_STYLE}
dihedral_style {DIHEDRAL_STYLE}
improper_style {IMPROPER_STYLE}
special_bonds {SPECIAL_BONDS}
pair_modify {PAIR_MODIFY}
neighbor {NEIGHBOR_SKIN} bin
neigh_modify {NEIGH_MODIFY}
neigh_modify one {NEIGH_ONE}
{GPU_PACKAGE}

{READ_COMMAND} {DATA_FILE}

# --- Unit conversion ---
variable        kcal2j  equal  4184.0
variable        NA      equal  6.02214076e23
variable        ang2m   equal  1.0e-10
variable        fs2s    equal  1.0e-15

# --- Geometry ---
variable        Nslabs  equal  {NEMD_N_SLABS}
variable        invslab equal  {NEMD_INVSLAB}
variable        Jarea   equal  {NEMD_AREA}

# --- Thermo Output ---
thermo_style custom step time temp press etotal ke pe ebond eangle edihed eimp evdwl ecoul elong etail vol lx ly lz density pxx pyy pzz
thermo_modify flush yes
thermo {THERMO_FREQ}

# --- Trajectory ---
dump dump_sc all custom {DUMP_FREQ} {DUMP_FILE} id type mol xs ys zs ix iy iz

# --- NVT pre-equilibration of supercell ---
timestep {TIMESTEP}
fix NVT_pre all nvt temp {T_TARGET} {T_TARGET} {T_DAMP}
run 10000
unfix NVT_pre
reset_timestep 0

# --- Müller-Plathe RNEMD Production on supercell ---
fix NVE all nve
fix mp all thermal/conductivity {NEMD_SWAP_FREQ} {NEMD_AXIS} {NEMD_N_SLABS}

compute layers all chunk/atom bin/1d {NEMD_AXIS} lower {NEMD_INVSLAB} units reduced
fix tprof all ave/chunk 1 {NEMD_SWAP_FREQ} {NEMD_SWAP_FREQ} layers temp density/mass file {TPROF_FILE} norm sample

thermo_style custom step time temp press etotal ke pe vol lx ly lz density f_mp
thermo_modify flush yes
thermo {THERMO_FREQ}

run {N_STEPS}

# --- Cleanup ---
unfix NVE
unfix mp
unfix tprof
uncompute layers
undump dump_sc

write_dump all custom {LAST_DUMP_FILE} id type mol x y z xu yu zu vx vy vz modify sort id
write_data {WRITE_DATA_FILE}

print "STAGE COMPLETE: NEMD supercell Muller-Plathe T={T_TARGET}K rep={NEMD_REP}x axis={NEMD_AXIS} steps={N_STEPS}"
quit
